## .NET Performance Analysis — `TimeSpanFormatting.cs`

**Context:** User confirmed this is a hot path (millions of log entries/min). All findings elevated accordingly.

### Scan Execution Checklist

| Recipe | Hits |
|--------|------|
| `.ToLower()`/`.ToUpper()` (no params) | 0 |
| `Enum.ToString()` + `.ToLowerInvariant()` | 1 |
| `.Substring(` | 0 |
| Chained `.Replace(` | 0 |
| `params ` | 1 |
| `.IndexOf`/`.StartsWith`/`.EndsWith`/`.Contains` missing `StringComparison` | 0 |
| LINQ operators (`.Select`/`.Where`/`.Take`/`.Aggregate`/`.Any`) | 16 |
| `.ToList()` | 1 |
| `.ToArray()` | 1 |
| `new List<` | 1 |
| `static readonly Dictionary<` / `FrozenDictionary<` | 0 / 0 |
| Unsealed non-abstract non-static classes | 1 |
| `sealed class` | 0 |
| Sync-over-async / `new Regex(` / `new HttpClient` / `JsonSerializerOptions` | 0 |

✅ No sync-over-async, regex, HttpClient, or serialization issues detected.

